Alpine-Kafka
Apache Kafka is a distributed event streaming platform that lets you publish, subscribe to, store, and process streams of events in real-time. This installation uses KRaft (Kafka Raft) mode, eliminating the need for Zookeeper.
https://kafka.apache.org/
https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/
https://github.com/apache/kafka

# Tags
alpine;messaging;streaming;bigdata;kraft

# Defaults
2
2048
8
alpine
3.20
1

# Ports
9092
9093

# Commands
kafka-topics.sh --bootstrap-server ${IP}:9092 --list
kafka-topics.sh --bootstrap-server ${IP}:9092 --create --topic mytopic --partitions 3 --replication-factor 1
kafka-console-producer.sh --bootstrap-server ${IP}:9092 --topic mytopic
kafka-console-consumer.sh --bootstrap-server ${IP}:9092 --topic mytopic --from-beginning
kafka-broker-api-versions.sh --bootstrap-server ${IP}:9092

# Notes
This installation uses KRaft mode, eliminating Zookeeper dependency
Port 9092 for Kafka broker, 9093 for controller
Single-node cluster configuration for simplicity
For production multi-node clusters, additional configuration needed
First broker in a KRaft-based cluster
Use kafka-topics.sh to create and manage topics